P(x) > 0
\forall x \in \mathbb{R}
 S={y^2+z^2=P^2(x)}\subset\mathbb{R}^3 
F(x,y,z) = \alpha x + \beta y + \gamma z
F
S
 H(x,y,z,\lambda) = \alpha x + \beta y + \gamma z - \lambda (P^2(x)-y^2-z^2) 
 \frac{\partial H}{\partial x} = \alpha - 2\lambda P(x) \frac{dP}{dx} = 0\\ \frac{\partial H}{\partial y} = \beta +2\lambda y = 0\\ \frac{\partial H}{\partial z} = \gamma +2\lambda z = 0\\ \frac{\partial H}{\partial \lambda} = 0=P^2(x)-y^2-z^2\\ 
